ads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic09.jpg\"},{\"id\":299,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic10.jpg\"},{\"id\":300,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic11.jpg\"},{\"id\":301,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic12.jpg\"},{\"id\":302,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic13.jpg\"},{\"id\":303,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic14.jpg\"},{\"id\":304,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic15.jpg\"},{\"id\":305,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic16.jpg\"},{\"id\":306,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic17.jpg\"},{\"id\":307,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic18.jpg\"},{\"id\":308,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic19.jpg\"},{\"id\":309,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic20.jpg\"},{\"id\":310,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic21.jpg\"},{\"id\":311,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic22.jpg\"}],\"galleries\":[{\"gallery_title\":\"New Gallery\",\"_id\":\"a77a9d5\"}],\"show_all_galleries_label\":\"All\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"gallery\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"43a3730\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"4d8b616\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"606810d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><strong>Dengkil \\u2013 Orang Asli \\u2013 Mobile Medical Camp \\u2013 13 January 2019<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<p>On 13 Jan 2019, we were privileged to serve the Orang Asli community in Dengkil, Selangor. Dengkil&nbsp;is a&nbsp;mukim&nbsp;in&nbsp;Sepang District,&nbsp;Selangor,&nbsp;Malaysia.<\\/p>\\n<p>The town lies between&nbsp;Cyberjaya&nbsp;and the&nbsp;Multimedia Super Corridor&nbsp;to the north, and&nbsp;Salak Tinggi&nbsp;to the south. Hidden between Putrajaya and Cyberjaya, a community of Temuan orang asli is living in isolation sandwiched by modern living. They have travel some 17km from their small wooden house to a government clinic in Dengkil if anyone fell ill.<\\/p>\\n<p>Early communications with village elders revealed that many of the members of the villagers were seeking medical screening and medical attention. Often, these orang asli communities are situated far from major cities and as a result, have a difficult time finding quality healthcare as they need it. These communities are often under served and as results they face various challenges living a normal life.<\\/p>\\n<p>A team was set up to run a mobile medical camp event at Dengkil. The team consisted of 9 doctors, 2 registered nurses, 3 pharmacists and a number of other volunteers from various backgrounds. Three of our volunteers travelled all the way from Singapore to participate in this camp. The objective of this medical camp was to provide free health screening on lifestyle related diseases and consultation based on patients\\u2019 needs The programme enables the community to undergo general health screening for non-communicable diseases such as diabetes and high blood pressure, among others.<\\/p>\\n<p>More than 90 individuals were screened, and the team took every effort to meet and address all of their medical concerns.&nbsp;We spoke about healthy lifestyle, healthy eating habits and also recorded the BMI and nourishment status of each child in the village. We will be monitoring these patients and do a follow up with then during our next visit.<\\/p>\\n<p>General conclusion drawn was that most children in this village do not have proper breakfast, having poor appetite and poor memory due to various reasons.<\\/p>\\n<p>The success of these camps depends on our volunteers. Their time, effort, and fundraising is what keeps these life-saving camps alive. Medical students who attend the camps report the experience as having a massive impact on their personal and professional development and find it very rewarding indeed.<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Statistics:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\n<p><ul><li>14 Medical volunteers<\\/li><li>10 auxiliary volunteers<\\/li><li>90 patients screened<\\/li><li>6 specialties offered<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"c7498bd\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ca1fbad\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"c11efb9\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"gallery\":[{\"id\":313,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic01.jpg\"},{\"id\":314,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic02.jpg\"},{\"id\":315,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic03.jpg\"},{\"id\":316,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic04.jpg\"},{\"id\":317,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic05.jpg\"},{\"id\":318,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic06.jpg\"},{\"id\":319,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic07.jpg\"},{\"id\":320,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic08.jpg\"},{\"id\":321,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalump