fully employed.<\\/p><p>We for the first time organized this free medical camp at Kalumpang Campus, co-organizing with Sai Ananda Nilayam. Sai Ananda Nilayam is a noble spiritual movement envisioned to provide voluntary medical assistance for almost 15 years. From bi-annual camps, they have grown to organize on a monthly basis and at times going to various remote regions of the country giving free medical assistance to people who are unable to get them.<\\/p><p>The town Kalumpang has a population of about 3,000. Slightly over an hour\\u2019s drive from Kuala Lumpur, the town sits on the fringe of Selangor and to some city dwellers, it is a retreat they escape to over the weekend. The whole town has a mixture of Malay and Chinese villages coming from diverse economic background.<\\/p><p>Medical screening and medical attention and awareness on good hygiene practices were given to the students of this campus. Many of our students were from dysfunctional environment that lack basic human values and personal hygiene. They face tremendous challenges to overcome these difficulties just to get back on track to lead a normal life.<\\/p><p>About 30 of the dedicated volunteers comprising of doctors, dentists, pharmacists, dermatologist , medical assistants and optometrist were present to provide their services. More than 150 students and local residents of Kalumpang town received the free medical screening and relevant medication from the medical officers.<\\/p><p><strong>Statistics:<\\/strong><\\/p><ul><li>30 Medical volunteers<\\/li><li>20 auxiliary volunteers<\\/li><li>150 patients screened<\\/li><li>6 specialties offered<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f73d704\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"36248b2\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"38f4aff\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\"