rl\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic12.jpg\"},{\"id\":397,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic13.jpg\"},{\"id\":398,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic14.jpg\"},{\"id\":399,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic15.jpg\"},{\"id\":400,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic16.jpg\"},{\"id\":401,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic17.jpg\"},{\"id\":402,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic18.jpg\"},{\"id\":403,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic19.jpg\"},{\"id\":404,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic20.jpg\"},{\"id\":405,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic21.jpg\"},{\"id\":406,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Dengkil-pic22.jpg\"}],\"galleries\":[{\"gallery_title\":\"New Gallery\",\"_id\":\"5b119b3\"}],\"show_all_galleries_label\":\"All\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"gallery\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"43a3730\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"4d8b616\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"606810d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><strong>Dengkil \\u2013 Orang Asli \\u2013 Mobile Medical Camp \\u2013 13 January 2019<\\/strong><\\/p><p>On 13 Jan 2019, we were privileged to serve the Orang Asli community in Dengkil, Selangor. Dengkil\\u00a0is a\\u00a0mukim\\u00a0in\\u00a0Sepang District,\\u00a0Selangor,\\u00a0Malaysia.<\\/p><p>The town lies between\\u00a0Cyberjaya\\u00a0and the\\u00a0Multimedia Super Corridor\\u00a0to the north, and\\u00a0Salak Tinggi\\u00a0to the south. Hidden between Putrajaya and Cyberjaya, a community of Temuan orang asli is living in isolation sandwiched by modern living. They have travel some 17km from their small wooden house to a government clinic in Dengkil if anyone fell ill.<\\/p><p>Early communications with village elders revealed that many of the members of the villagers were seeking medical screening and medical attention. Often, these orang asli communities are situated far from major cities and as a result, have a difficult time finding quality healthcare as they need it. These communities are often under served and as results they face various challenges living a normal life.<\\/p><p>A team was set up to run a mobile medical camp event at Dengkil. The team consisted of 9 doctors, 2 registered nurses, 3 pharmacists and a number of other volunteers from various backgrounds. Three of our volunteers travelled all the way from Singapore to participate in this camp. The objective of this medical camp was to provide free health screening on lifestyle related diseases and consultation based on patients\\u2019 needs The programme enables the community to undergo general health screening for non-communicable diseases such as diabetes and high blood pressure, among others.<\\/p><p>More than 90 individuals were screened, and the team took every effort to meet and address all of their medical concerns.\\u00a0We spoke about healthy lifestyle, healthy eating habits and also recorded the BMI and nourishment status of each child in the village. We will be monitoring these patients and do a follow up with then during our next visit.<\\/p><p>General conclusion drawn was that most children in this village do not have proper breakfast, having poor appetite and poor memory due to various reasons.<\\/p><p>The success of these camps depends on our volunteers. Their time, effort, and fundraising is what keeps these life-saving camps alive. Medical students who attend the camps report the experience as having a massive impact on their personal and professional development and find it very rewarding indeed.<\\/p><p><strong>Statistics:<\\/strong><\\/p><ul><li>14 Medical volunteers<\\/li><li>10 auxiliary volunteers<\\/li><li>90 patients screened<\\/li><li>6 specialties offered<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f6f10f9\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7297c65\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d2eeaca\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"gallery\":[{\"id\":361,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic01.jpg\"},{\"id\":380,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic20.jpg\"},{\"id\":379,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic19.jpg\"},{\"id\":378,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic18.jpg\"},{\"id\":377,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic17.jpg\"},{\"id\":376,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic16.jpg\"},{\"id\":375,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic15.jpg\"},{\"id\":374,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic14.jpg\"},{\"id\":373,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic13.jpg\"},{\"id\":372,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic12.jpg\"},{\"id\":371,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic11.jpg\"},{\"id\":370,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic10.jpg\"},{\"id\":369,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic09.jpg\"},{\"id\":368,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic08.jpg\"},{\"id\":367,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic07.jpg\"},{\"id\":366,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic06.jpg\"},{\"id\":365,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic05.jpg\"},{\"id\":364,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic04.jpg\"},{\"id\":363,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic03.jpg\"},{\"id\":362,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/one.wordpress.test\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/Kalumpang-pic02.jpg\"}],\"galleries\":[{\"gallery_title\":\"New Gallery\",\"_id\":\"5e2851f\"}],\"show_all_galleries_label\":\"All\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"gallery\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"ebc937f\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f6ca0b8\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f81361c\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><strong>Kalumpang - Mobile Medical Camp \\u2013 23 June 2019<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Kalumpang Campus is under the auspices of MySkills Foundation of Malaysia who are working towards transforming At-Risk Youths, equipping them with the right skills and placing them with proper jobs so they can be gainfully employed.<\\/p><p>We for the first time organized this free medical camp at Kalumpang Campus, co-organizing with Sai Ananda Nilayam. Sai Ananda Nilayam is a noble spiritual movement envisioned to provide voluntary medical assistance for almost 15 years. From bi-annual camps, they have grown to organize on a monthly basis and at times going to various remote regions of the country giving free medical assistance to people who are unable to get them.<\\/p><p>The town Kalumpang has a population of about 3,000. Slightly over an hour\\u2019s drive from Kuala Lumpur, the town sits on the fringe of Selangor and to some city dwellers, it is a retreat they escape to over the weekend. The whole town has a mixture of Malay and Chinese villages coming from diverse economic background.<\\/p><p>Medical screening and medical attention and awareness on good hygiene practices were given to the students of this campus. Many of our students were from dysfunctional environment that lack basic human values and personal hygiene. They face tremendous challenges to overcome these difficulties just to get back on track to lead a normal life.<\\/p><p>About 30 of the dedicated volunteers comprising of doctors, dentists, pharmacists, dermatologist , medical assistants and optometrist were present to provide their services. More than 150 students and local residents of Kalumpang town received the free medical screening and relevant medication from the medical officers.<\\/p><p><strong>Statistics:<\\/strong><\\/p><ul><li>30 Medical volunteers<\\/li><li>20 auxiliary volunteers<\\/li><li>150 patients screened<\\/li><li>6 specialties offered<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f73d704\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"36248b2\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"38f4aff\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><strong>CONTACTS<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"align\":\"center\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"0f4a2c0\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"bcb5ed1\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\"